<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ideee1e106-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s1639j"><num value="1639j">§ 1639j.</num><heading> Exclusion from Federal preemption</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this subchapter, subchapter V, or any regulation, rule, or requirement promulgated in accordance with this subchapter or subchapter V shall be construed to preempt any remedy created by a State or Federal statutory or common law right.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ideee1e107-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1946-08-14/ch966">Aug. 14, 1946, ch. 966</ref>, title II, § 296, as added <ref href="/us/pl/114/216/s1">Pub. L. 114–216, § 1</ref>, <date date="2016-07-29">July 29, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/838">130 Stat. 838</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
